-- Detroit Lions’ Nate Burleson Out for NFL Season With Broken Leg
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-10-24T04:43:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/detroit-lions-nate-burleson-out-for-nfl-season-with-broken-leg.html
Nate Burleson will miss the rest of
the National Football League season after breaking his leg in
 Detroit ’s 13-7 loss at  Chicago  on Oct. 22, Lions coach Jim Schwartz said.  Wide receiver Burleson, 31, was injured in the third
quarter as he was tackled on a 16-yard reception. He tried to
stand and fell back to the ground.  Second-year receiver Titus Young and rookie Ryan Broyles
will move into Burleson’s spot for the remainder of the season.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
